<script type="text/javascript">

// This function takes an Id for a container that wraps a client widget (Help, Payments, etc)
// It applies behaviour style if the client widget chooses to.
// Whatever shared behaviour needs to be defined for clients, should be contained in this function.
function triggerClientBehavior(clientContainerId) {
    var clientContainer = jQuery('#' + clientContainerId);

    // If an external container is defined, allow the client to hide it until content is available.
    if (clientContainer) clientContainer.attr('style', 'display:block'); 
}

function renderTopQuestions(questionIds, questionTranslations, containerDivId, questionsCache) {
    var containerDiv = jQuery('#' + containerDivId);
    
    var questionsList = jQuery(document.createElement('ul'));
    questionsList.attr('id', 'questionsList');
    for(var i = 0; i < questionIds.length; i++) {
        questionsCache[containerDivId][i] = false;

        var questionRow = jQuery(document.createElement('li'));
        questionRow.attr('id', containerDivId + '_questionrow_' + i);
        var questionSpan = jQuery(document.createElement('span'));
        var questionLink = jQuery(document.createElement('a'));

        questionLink.attr('href', '#');
        questionLink.html(questionTranslations[i]);
        questionSpan.addClass('questionsText');

        questionSpan.attr('id', containerDivId + '_question_' + i);
        questionSpan.attr('questionNumber', i);
        questionSpan.attr('worldStringId', questionIds[i]);
        questionSpan.append(questionLink);
        questionRow.append(questionSpan);
        questionsList.append(questionRow);
    }
    questionsList.appendTo(containerDiv); 
}



// This function takes a questionId, fetches an answer for this questionId via
// an ajax call, and populate the answerSpan with this answer.
function fetchAnswer(questionId, questionTranslation, questionNumber, language, answerSpanId,
                     containerDivId, trackPrefix, predictionId,sourceId) {
    var answerBody = jQuery('#' + answerSpanId);
    answerBody.html("Loading...");
    jQuery.ajax({
        url: "https://sellercentral.amazon.co.uk/gp/case-dashboard/ajax/display-seldon-answer.html",
        data: {
            'ref_': 'wd_ph_qst',
            'predictionId' : predictionId,
            'questionWorldStringId' : questionId, 
            'language' : language,
            'sourceId' : sourceId
        },
        type: "POST",
        cache: false,
        dataType: 'json',
        success: function(ajaxResponse) {
            var response = eval(ajaxResponse)[0];
            if(!response["helpContent"]) {
                answerBody.html("We're sorry. There was a problem retrieving information for this question. Please try again later.");
            } else {
                questionsCache[containerDivId][questionNumber] = true;
                answerBody.html(response["helpContent"]);
                answerBody.append(createHMDDiv(answerBody, questionId, trackPrefix, predictionId));
            }
         }, 
         error: function(request, status, error) {
            if (request.responseText.indexOf("<title>") > -1) {
                window.location.href="/gp/contact-us/contact-amazon-form.html?urlStr=%2Fgp%2Fhomepage.html&ref=id_contactus_foot_home";
            } else {
                answerBody.html("We're sorry. There was a problem retrieving information for this question. Please try again later.");
            }
         }, 
         complete: function() {
         }
    });
}

// function to log user satisfaction with omniture.
function logUserSatisfaction(questionId, isUserSatisfied, trackPrefix, predictionId) {
    s.linkTrackVars =
        "prop3,prop8,prop9,prop10,prop16,prop17,prop18,prop11,prop21,prop40,channel"; 
    s.prop16 = questionId;
    s.prop21 = 'v1';
    s.tl(true, 'o', trackPrefix + 'User Satisfied : ' + isUserSatisfied);
    jQuery.ajax({
        url:  "https://sellercentral.amazon.co.uk/gp/case-dashboard/ajax/log-user-satisfaction.html",
        data: {
            'predictionId' : predictionId,
            'questionId' : questionId,
            'isUserSatisfied' : isUserSatisfied
        },
        type: "POST",
        cache: false
    });
}

// create and return a div that contains Yes and No links.
function createHMDDiv(answerSpan, questionId, trackPrefix, predictionId) {
    var hmdDiv = jQuery(document.createElement('div'));
    hmdDiv.attr('id', 'hmd_'+questionId);
    hmdDiv.attr('class', 'hmdDiv');
    var hmdText = jQuery(document.createElement('b'));
    hmdText.html("Did this answer your question?"); 
    hmdDiv.append(hmdText);

    var hmdLinks = jQuery(document.createElement('ul'));
    var hmdYes = jQuery(document.createElement('li'));
    var hmdYesLink = jQuery(document.createElement('a'));
    hmdYesLink.attr('href', '#');
    hmdYesLink.html("Yes");
    hmdYesLink.click(function () {
        answerSpan.hide();
        answerSpan.attr('status', 'hidden');
        answerSpan.prev().removeClass('questionSelected');
        logUserSatisfaction(questionId,'Yes', trackPrefix, predictionId);
    });
    hmdYes.append(hmdYesLink);
    var hmdNo = jQuery(document.createElement('li'));
    var hmdNoLink = jQuery(document.createElement('a'));
    hmdNoLink.attr('href', '#');
    hmdNoLink.html("No");
    hmdNoLink.click(function() {
            answerSpan.hide();
            answerSpan.attr('status', 'hidden');
            answerSpan.prev().removeClass('questionSelected');
            logUserSatisfaction(questionId,'No', trackPrefix, predictionId);
    });
    hmdNo.append(hmdNoLink);
    hmdLinks.append(hmdYes);
    hmdLinks.append(hmdNo);
    hmdDiv.append(hmdLinks);
    return hmdDiv;
}

// function to create spans for answers 
// and append these to the correponding question divs
function createAnswerSpans(containerDivId, numQuestions) {
      for(var i = 0; i < numQuestions; i++) {
          var questionRow = jQuery('#' + containerDivId + '_questionrow_' + i);
          var questionSpan = jQuery('#' + containerDivId + '_question_' + i);
          var answerSpan = jQuery(document.createElement('span'));
          answerSpan.attr('id', containerDivId + '_answer_' + i);
          answerSpan.attr('status', 'hidden');
          answerSpan.addClass('answer');
          questionRow.append(answerSpan);
          questionSpan.attr('answerSpan', containerDivId + '_answer_' + i);
      }
  
  }
  
  
  
// function to add onClick event to the question Divs. 
// When a question is clicked for the first time, make an ajax call to fetch the answer
// afterwards just show and hide the answer div.
function linkQuestionAnswer (containerDivId, questionsIds, questionTranslations, numQuestions, questionsCache,
                            trackPrefix, predictionId,sourceId) {
    for(var i = 0; i < numQuestions; i++) {
        var questionSpan = jQuery('#' + containerDivId + '_question_' + i);
        questionSpan.click(function() {
            var answerId = jQuery(this).attr('answerSpan');
            var answerNumber =jQuery(this).attr('questionNumber');
            var answer = jQuery('#'+answerId);
        
            //Collapse other answers when clicking and expanding one answer
            for(var j = 0; j < numQuestions; j++) {
                var questionSpanTmp = jQuery('#' + containerDivId + '_question_' + j);
                var answerIdTmp = jQuery(questionSpanTmp).attr('answerSpan');
                if (answerId != answerIdTmp){
                    var answerTmp = jQuery('#' + answerIdTmp);
                    if (answerTmp.attr('status') != 'hidden'){
                        answerTmp.hide();
                        answerTmp.attr('status', 'hidden');
                        jQuery(questionSpanTmp).removeClass('questionSelected');
                    }
                }
            }

            if(answer.attr('status') == 'hidden') {
                if(!questionsCache[containerDivId][answerNumber]) {
                    fetchAnswer(questionsIds[answerNumber], questionTranslations[answerNumber], answerNumber, language,
                                answerId, containerDivId, trackPrefix, predictionId,sourceId);
                    s.linkTrackVars =
                        "prop3,prop8,prop9,prop10,prop16,prop17,prop18,prop11,prop21,prop40,channel"; 
                    s.prop16 = questionsIds[answerNumber];
		    s.prop21 = 'v1';
                    s.tl(true, 'o', trackPrefix + 'User Clicked on Top Questions');
                } 
                answer.show();
                answer.attr('status', 'visible');
                jQuery(this).addClass('questionSelected');

                
            } else {
                answer.hide();
                answer.attr('status', 'hidden');
                jQuery(this).removeClass('questionSelected');
            }
        });
    }
}
</script>

      <script type="text/javascript">
      var containerDivId = 'seldon-questions-content';
      var language = 'en_DE';
      var topQuestionsObject;
      var questionsCache = new Array(); 
      var numQuestions;
      var questionWorldStringIds;
      var questionTranslatedStrings;
      var fromWidget;
      var usePredefinedQuestions;
      var trackPrefix;

       amznJQ.onReady('JQuery', function(){
          jQuery.ajax({
            url: "https://sellercentral.amazon.co.uk/gp/case-dashboard/ajax/get-top-questions.html",
            data: {
              'ref_': 'wd_ph_pred',
              'sourceId': 'PAYMENTS',
              'featureSets': '["M@_PRO","M@_PRO_FBA","M@_PRO_CLICK_WITHIN_ADVERTISER","M@_PRO_FBA_BASIC","M@_PRO_ACTIVE"]',
              'primaryFeature': 'SILVER',
              'sellerType' : 'PRO',
              'merchantId': 'A2OSGCAE4WEZ1P',
              'sessionId': '275-4296466-1340852',
              'numQuestions': '5',
              'showPredefinedQuestions': '1',
              'referrerUrl': "/gp/payments-account/date-range-reports.html"
            },
            type: "POST",
            cache: true,
            dataType: 'json',
            success: function(jsonResponse) {
                processTopQustionsResponse (jsonResponse)
            },
            error: function(request, status, error) {
              // display nothing
              console.log("get-top-questions: Error parsing JSON response: " + error);
            },
            complete: function() {
              // display nothing
            }
          });
        });



    function processTopQustionsResponse (jsonResponse)
    {
          var predictionId;
          topQuestionsObject = eval(jsonResponse)[0];

          if (topQuestionsObject && topQuestionsObject['predictionId']) {
            predictionId = topQuestionsObject['predictionId'];
            if (jQuery("#predictionId")) jQuery("#predictionId").val(predictionId); 
          }

          if(topQuestionsObject && topQuestionsObject['topQuestions']) {
            questionWorldStringIds = topQuestionsObject['topQuestions'];
            questionTranslatedStrings = topQuestionsObject['translatedQuestions'];
            usePredefinedQuestions = topQuestionsObject['usePredefinedQuestions'];
            numQuestions = questionWorldStringIds.length;
            questionsCache[containerDivId] = new Array(numQuestions);

            renderTopQuestions(questionWorldStringIds, questionTranslatedStrings, containerDivId, questionsCache);
            createAnswerSpans(containerDivId, numQuestions);
            if (1 == 1){
                trackPrefix = "PHW Pay PH ";
            } else{
                trackPrefix = "Contact Us PH ";
            }

            linkQuestionAnswer(containerDivId, questionWorldStringIds,questionTranslatedStrings, numQuestions,
                               questionsCache, trackPrefix, predictionId,'PAYMENTS');

          }
    }
    </script>
  </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
	amznJQ.onReady('JQuery', function() {

	var resizeOnSize = '800';
 	
	function onResize() {
		if(window.innerWidth < resizeOnSize || document.body.offsetWidth < resizeOnSize) {
			$('#left-side').css('float','none');
			$('#left-side').css('width','auto');
			$('#predictive-help').css('width','250px');
			$('#predictive-help').css('max-width','none');
			$('#predictive-help').css('margin-top','30px');
			$('#ad').css('margin-right','0');
			$('.pPaymentButtons').css('width','auto');
		}
		else {
			$('#left-side').css('float','left');
				$('#left-side').css('width','78%');
			$('#predictive-help').css('width','auto');
			$('#predictive-help').css('max-width','20%');
			$('#predictive-help').css('margin-top','76px');
			$('#ad').css('margin-right','-25%');
			$('.pPaymentButtons').css('width','790px');
		}
	}
	onResize();
	$(window).resize(function () { 
		onResize();
	});
		});
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function changeLanguage(list) {
    var language = list.options[list.selectedIndex].value,
	location = encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);

    if (language) {
	window.location.href = "/gp/switch-language.html?formSubmitted=true&language=" + language + "&location=" + location; 
    }
}
</script>

<form name="switchLanguage" style="display:inline">
<select onchange="changeLanguage(this.form.elements[0])">
       <option value="de_DE">Deutsch</option>
       <option value="en_DE" selected="selected">English</option>
       <option value="zh_CN">����</option>
</select>
</form>
